                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In n(omine) D(omi)ni. Constat me <persName key="#Archdeacons"><name
                                ref="Becio">Becio</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Archdeacons">archidiac(o)n(us)</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/1498">s(an)c(t)e Cumiaclens(i)s
                            Eccl(esi)e</orgName>, iubente do(mi)no <persName key="#Bishops"
                            ref="#people/1570">Georgius</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">ep(iscopu)s</rs> ite(m) s(an)c(t)e Cumiacl(e)ns(i)s
                        Eccl(esi)e, accepisse accepi a vob(is) <persName key="#Priests"><name
                                ref="Albinus">Albinus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">pr(es)b(iter)</rs> p(e)n(sionem) de una <rs key="#Houses"
                            >mansione</rs> cu(m) <rs key="#Curtes">curte</rs> iuxta se abente(m)
                        q(ui) e(st) p(o)s(ita) in <placeName ref="#places/485">Cumiaclo</placeName>,
                        in regione <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/1481">S(an)c(t)e Marie q(ui)
                            v(ocatur) Fermosa</orgName>, que(m) p(er) <rs
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis">enfiteusin</rs> tenere viso estis
                        at [iura] n(ost)ra eccl(esi)a, om(n)iq(ue) ann(o) in festivitate s(an)c(t)i
                        Cassiani p(e)n(sionem) <rs key="#Rent_in_money">d(e)n(ariorum) tres</rs>
                        t(an)t(um). Unde p(ro) munimine v(est)ro feci vob(is) hoc deaccepto in
                        m(en)se aug(usto), indic(tione) p(r)ima, Cumiaclo.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
